1
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:03,867
<i>I had no accomplice
in a crime I never committed!</i>

2
00:00:03,967 --> 00:00:05,633
<i> It's impossible for the body</i>

3
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,067
<i>- Freeze! Hands in the air!
- to end up there on its own!</i>

4
00:00:08,167 --> 00:00:10,567
<i>I was the last one with him
before he died.</i>

5
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:12,067
<i> And he himself told me</i>

6
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:14,100
<i>that Uncle Andy's men
had kidnapped him.</i>

7
00:00:14,267 --> 00:00:15,367
<i> Please, Mr. Arellano,</i>

8
00:00:15,467 --> 00:00:17,367
<i>you are not welcome here
in Hotel 88.</i>

9
00:00:17,467 --> 00:00:20,033
<i>How do we make Andy pay
for all the crimes he committed?</i>

10
00:00:20,133 --> 00:00:21,867
<i> We need to find the treasure.</i>

11
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:24,600
<i> Let's begin searching for it.</i>

12
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:25,600
<i> Did you hear that?</i>

13
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:26,733
<i> Could it be a guest?</i>

14
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:27,767
<i> What was that?</i>

15
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:29,600
<i> Did you hear that, too?</i>

16
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:33,700
<i> My son...</i>

17
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:38,400
<i> Who killed you?!</i>

18
00:00:43,267 --> 00:00:46,900
[ANDY] Look, I figured you
wouldn't like the food here,

19
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,900
so I had the helper
prepare some.

20
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:51,967
As for the fruits, I know
you'll need them here.

21
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:53,667
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

22
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,167
[LEON] What are you doing?

23
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,433
I'm visiting you.

24
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,467
Don't you like my presents?

25
00:01:01,433 --> 00:01:03,233
I don't need any of them.

26
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:06,300
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

27
00:01:06,467 --> 00:01:08,300
I thought you might say that.

28
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:12,100
So I brought something else
that you need.

29
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:18,200
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

30
00:01:18,367 --> 00:01:19,833
That was Justin, right?

31
00:01:19,967 --> 00:01:20,933
[MUSIC BECOMES OMINOUS]

32
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:22,633
He was talking to the victim
who was found

33
00:01:22,733 --> 00:01:24,167
in the back of your car.

34
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:26,833
[ANDY] Now,

35
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:29,100
to those who will see it,

36
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:32,333
they might think that
Justin is the real killer.

37
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:38,000
On the other hand,
some people might think that...

38
00:01:38,167 --> 00:01:39,833
you were in cahoots
with your own brother.

39
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:43,500
You know, to each
his own interpretation.

40
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:48,133
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:51,133
That doesn't prove Justin was
the one who killed Juan.

42
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:53,333
I didn't say I was going
to release it.

43
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,833
I can keep this
with me forever.

44
00:01:56,733 --> 00:01:58,200
But there's a trade-off.

45
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:01,233
You know how this goes.
We give and take.

46
00:02:04,433 --> 00:02:06,133
Damn you!

47
00:02:06,233 --> 00:02:08,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

48
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,633
[SIGHING DEEPLY]

49
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,700
I'm sorry, Leon.

50
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,667
I hate that it came to this,

51
00:02:16,733 --> 00:02:18,233
but we are still family.

52
00:02:26,067 --> 00:02:27,833
- [BANGS TABLE]
- [BREATHES SHARPLY]

53
00:02:31,767 --> 00:02:38,667
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

54
00:03:31,367 --> 00:03:33,900
<i> Please don't sell Hotel 88.</i>

55
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:38,000
<i> Not just for the business,</i>

56
00:03:38,167 --> 00:03:39,800
<i> not for the money.</i>

57
00:03:40,433 --> 00:03:42,433
<i> But because this is your home.</i>

58
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:45,300
<i> And I want you to know...</i>

59
00:03:45,467 --> 00:03:48,300
[KIKO] We keep replaying the
video until the broken part,

60
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:49,833
but nothing works.

61
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,833
Can't we get someone else
to help?

62
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,333
You know, send it for repair.

63
00:03:54,533 --> 00:03:56,833
Maybe only a professional
can fix it.

64
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,433
[KIKO] Jade, we can't do that.

65
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:02,800
We could get unlucky
and trust the wrong person.

66
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:05,167
The details are just
far too precious to risk.

67
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:06,600
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

68
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:07,633
Kiko...

69
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:09,833
I can't seem to solve anything.

70
00:04:09,967 --> 00:04:11,800
My brother is in prison.

71
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:13,367
And now this video...

72
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:15,133
I don't know, Kiko.
This might be it.

73
00:04:15,233 --> 00:04:16,933
[KIKO] Hey, pull yourself
together, Jade.

74
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:19,667
A little bit
of positive vibes, okay?

75
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:23,667
I'm sure Leon
will be released soon.

76
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:30,633
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

77
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:44,533
So, have you...

78
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:46,500
Have you talked to Edward?

79
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:53,700
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:04:55,067 --> 00:04:56,233
[KIKO] Right.

81
00:04:57,433 --> 00:04:59,367
Finding the right moment
is hard

82
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:02,233
when you're with Luna
and Justin all the time.

83
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:06,400
They're still not willing
to listen.

84
00:05:07,067 --> 00:05:08,500
[KIKO] I would be, too, Jade.

85
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,533
If it happened to Cheska...

86
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,400
I'm not saying Edward
is a bad person,

87
00:05:15,533 --> 00:05:18,833
but your siblings really
just want to protect you.

88
00:05:20,367 --> 00:05:21,767
I know that.

89
00:05:23,433 --> 00:05:24,733
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

90
00:05:25,967 --> 00:05:27,233
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

91
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:32,700
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

92
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:33,567
Excuse me.

93
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,567
- I'll just use the restroom.
- Okay.

94
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:37,867
[DOOR OPENS]

95
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:40,700
[DOOR CLOSES]

96
00:05:43,433 --> 00:05:44,767
What?

97
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:47,733
Now you want Andy
to be part of Hotel 88?

98
00:05:48,733 --> 00:05:49,800
[SIGHS]

99
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:53,467
Did he threaten you
into changing your mind?

100
00:05:53,633 --> 00:05:54,467
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

101
00:05:54,633 --> 00:05:57,367
He knows about Justin and Juan.

102
00:05:57,900 --> 00:06:00,467
Haven't you realized that
he's pushing you into a corner

103
00:06:00,633 --> 00:06:03,600
because he's so desperate
to grab Hotel 88?

104
00:06:05,067 --> 00:06:06,433
I thought about that.

105
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:09,933
But if we don't give
Uncle Andy what he wants,

106
00:06:10,133 --> 00:06:11,967
he'll drag Justin into this.

107
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:14,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

108
00:06:14,767 --> 00:06:17,767
We're looking for evidence
so you can get you out of here.

109
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:19,967
We don't have to give in
to his demand.

110
00:06:20,467 --> 00:06:21,933
Martin, please.

111
00:06:22,033 --> 00:06:24,500
If it were just me,
I would fight for it.

112
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:26,567
But he's willing to play Justin
as his ace.

113
00:06:26,667 --> 00:06:28,500
- My siblings.
- Leon.

114
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:31,467
Leon, have a little faith.

115
00:06:31,633 --> 00:06:33,967
The lawyers are already
taking care of everything.

116
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:35,500
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

117
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:38,067
But what if Andy
released Justin's video?

118
00:06:38,167 --> 00:06:39,633
[MARTIN] He's a demon!

119
00:06:42,533 --> 00:06:43,800
You know, Leon...

120
00:06:44,233 --> 00:06:45,667
If Andy wants to play games,

121
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,933
then we're going
to do the same.

122
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:50,533
We won't have to lose Hotel 88,

123
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:53,833
and we'll get your siblings
out of this mess.

124
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,367
[MARTIN] Do you understand?

125
00:06:56,533 --> 00:07:01,367
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

126
00:07:01,533 --> 00:07:03,467
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

127
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:05,600
[MUSIC FADING]

128
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,700
- Edward.
- Jade.

129
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:17,300
Edward, what are you
doing here?

130
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,867
My siblings are here.

131
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,167
Jade, I just wanted
to clarify some things.

132
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:23,467
No one's telling me
what's going on.

133
00:07:23,567 --> 00:07:25,333
You don't even talk to me.

134
00:07:25,433 --> 00:07:28,167
Edward, my siblings are
always around.

135
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:31,233
Jade, explain it to me.

136
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:33,533
I need to hear it
from you, please.

137
00:07:34,233 --> 00:07:37,033
What did my dad do to make
everyone angry with him?

138
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,167
[SIGHS]

139
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:40,367
Edward, it's not that simple.

140
00:07:41,067 --> 00:07:43,167
Can we please stop
talking about this?

141
00:07:43,267 --> 00:07:44,900
I don't want any more trouble.

142
00:07:45,767 --> 00:07:49,133
The problem won't fix itself
unless we talk about it.

143
00:07:52,367 --> 00:07:53,600
Edward...

144
00:07:56,467 --> 00:07:58,933
Luna and Justin's suspicions...

145
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,767
Do you share them, too?

146
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:08,233
Yes.

147
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:10,233
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

148
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,433
That's why
I didn't want you to know.

149
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:18,500
Jade.

150
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:21,567
[EDWARD] If my dad helped Leon
get his freedom back,

151
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:23,233
would that change their minds?

152
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:26,067
I'm going to do that.
I'll talk to my dad.

153
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:28,933
No, Edward.

154
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:31,800
[Jade] At this point,

155
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:34,200
it'd be better if you pretended
not to know anything.

156
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:35,700
Okay?

157
00:08:36,733 --> 00:08:38,600
But, Jade, it doesn't have
to change the way

158
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:40,467
things are between us, right?

159
00:08:40,633 --> 00:08:43,933
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

160
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,100
Right?

161
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:48,467
Jade.

162
00:08:48,633 --> 00:08:49,933
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

163
00:08:56,433 --> 00:08:57,967
- You should go, Edward.
- J-Jade...

164
00:08:58,133 --> 00:08:59,300
- I have to go back now.
- Let's talk.

165
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:00,333
They're looking for me.

166
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:02,133
- Jade, just talk to me.
- Come on, Edward.

167
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,400
Go home.

168
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,133
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:09:05,267 --> 00:09:06,300
Go away.

170
00:09:09,367 --> 00:09:10,600
Jade.

171
00:09:17,167 --> 00:09:18,133
Jade.

172
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:25,167
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

173
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:30,800
Fix up something ahead of time
tomorrow for Leon.

174
00:09:30,967 --> 00:09:33,800
For Justin and Jade, always
keep food waiting at home.

175
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:36,300
Don't start cooking only
when they're on the way.

176
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,533
Yes, ma'am.

177
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,433
Thank you.

178
00:09:42,467 --> 00:09:43,533
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

179
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,100
Here. Just one bottle.

180
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,833
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:52,833
[BOTTLE THUDS]

182
00:09:54,067 --> 00:09:55,500
[GULPING]

183
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:10,033
[BOTH GULPING]

184
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:15,200
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

185
00:10:15,367 --> 00:10:16,900
I miss Leon.

186
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,467
[GULPING CONTINUES]

187
00:10:30,167 --> 00:10:32,533
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

188
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:35,700
- [WIND WHOOSHING]
- [CHIMES TINKLING]

189
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:37,267
[CURTAINS FLUTTERING]

190
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:41,767
- Mom!
- Mom!

191
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:42,867
Mom!

192
00:10:43,533 --> 00:10:45,033
- Mom!
- Mom...

193
00:10:48,067 --> 00:10:49,067
[FRIDA SIGHS]

194
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:52,400
Why didn't you tell us
anything, Mom?

195
00:10:52,567 --> 00:10:54,400
I thought you were going
to come home tomorrow.

196
00:10:54,567 --> 00:10:56,100
My flight got rescheduled.

197
00:10:56,233 --> 00:10:57,867
Plus, I didn't want
to bother any of you.

198
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:01,533
[VOICE BREAKS] I'm home.

199
00:11:01,967 --> 00:11:03,200
We missed you, Ma.

200
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:04,867
[SNIFFLING]

201
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:06,000
[FRIDA EXHALES DEEPLY]

202
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:11,533
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:14,533
[HENRI]<i> Leon insists that
</i> he never knew Juan.

204
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:18,133
<i>"I believe the person
who kidnapped me</i>

205
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:19,533
<i> was Leon Almazan."</i>

206
00:11:19,633 --> 00:11:23,600
[MARINA] How did Juan Soliman's
body end up in your car?

207
00:11:25,433 --> 00:11:27,200
[LEON] I don't know!

208
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,400
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

209
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,867
[HENRI]<i> If they really
</i> didn't know each other,

210
00:11:32,133 --> 00:11:35,300
<i>why did Juan say that he
had been kidnapped by Leon?</i>

211
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,700
[MUSIC FADING]

212
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:43,067
- [WHIMPERING, SNIFFLING]
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

213
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:45,433
Are you okay here?

214
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,067
I'm fine, Mom.

215
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,800
Are you guys safe?

216
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:54,767
[FRIDA] Don't worry about us
because we're together,

217
00:11:54,867 --> 00:11:57,767
but you... [SOBBING]

218
00:11:58,167 --> 00:11:59,467
Mom...

219
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:01,600
[BREATHES DEEPLY]
Don't worry.

220
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:03,933
I'll do everything

221
00:12:04,833 --> 00:12:07,233
to get you out
as soon as possible.

222
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:09,433
We will be together again.

223
00:12:11,133 --> 00:12:12,000
Okay?

224
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:15,467
[SNIFFLES]

225
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:20,800
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

226
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:23,867
[FRIDA] Leon...

227
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:28,300
I will do my best
to get you out of here.

228
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:34,933
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:36,267
Son,

230
00:12:36,367 --> 00:12:37,967
how did this happen to you?

231
00:12:39,667 --> 00:12:42,300
Who is that man?
Why are you being accused?

232
00:12:42,467 --> 00:12:44,167
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

233
00:12:44,333 --> 00:12:45,467
What did they tell you?

234
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:47,833
Nothing.

235
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:50,733
I wanted to hear
everything from you.

236
00:12:52,933 --> 00:12:54,167
I don't know, Mom.

237
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,667
[BREATHES SHAPLY]
I don't know him.

238
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:58,733
[EXHALES, HANDCUFF THUDS]

239
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:00,733
But I'm sure

240
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:03,033
Uncle Andy is responsible
for this.

241
00:13:03,733 --> 00:13:04,633
Andy?

242
00:13:05,933 --> 00:13:06,867
What?

243
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:09,333
Why?

244
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:12,900
Because I didn't want him
to be a partner in Hotel 88.

245
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:16,400
Can I ask why...

246
00:13:16,533 --> 00:13:18,133
why you didn't want to?

247
00:13:19,367 --> 00:13:21,000
He wants to be
a part of Hotel 88

248
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:23,533
and kick us all out.

249
00:13:24,933 --> 00:13:26,000
It's Andy.

250
00:13:26,567 --> 00:13:29,500
You know, he was
your Dad's close friend.

251
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:32,033
And then he did this to you?

252
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:33,700
Shouldn't he be the one in jail?

253
00:13:36,267 --> 00:13:37,200
I know.

254
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:40,000
But I don't have any evidence.

255
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:43,567
Everything the police got,
everything leads to me.

256
00:13:43,733 --> 00:13:48,767
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

257
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:51,067
Leon said that he wants
Uncle Andy to be a partner?

258
00:13:51,633 --> 00:13:52,733
[JUSTIN] No way.

259
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,667
He doesn't get to have
a final say on everything.

260
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,900
Leon is just thinking
about your safety.

261
00:13:57,567 --> 00:13:59,300
- Your family's safety.
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

262
00:13:59,433 --> 00:14:00,567
And you agreed?

263
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:01,767
Of course not.

264
00:14:01,933 --> 00:14:04,867
I told him we will do everything
to keep the hotel

265
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:06,867
and no one else will get
dragged into that mess.

266
00:14:07,933 --> 00:14:09,467
[JUSTIN]
This is all because of me.

267
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:11,433
Of that video.

268
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,933
I should have been more careful.

269
00:14:14,667 --> 00:14:15,933
[GIO] You weren't aware.

270
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:17,900
Andy is simply an animal.

271
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,400
He'll take advantage
of the situation

272
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,867
just to get what he wants.

273
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:28,067
I'll try to talk to Uncle Andy.

274
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:29,133
Luna.

275
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:31,500
Our lawyer said
to stay away from that family.

276
00:14:31,633 --> 00:14:33,733
[LUNA]
This is what Leon wants, Justin.

277
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,167
We can fool him.

278
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:40,233
He really thought
he's the only one

279
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,567
who could deceive people.

280
00:14:41,667 --> 00:14:43,233
Well then, let's play his game.

281
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:44,600
But how?

282
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,000
[GIO] Luna can talk to Andy.

283
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:50,633
Invite him to become
a partner in the hotel.

284
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:51,800
You'll tell him
you can't do it right away.

285
00:14:51,967 --> 00:14:53,633
We just need a break from him.

286
00:14:55,367 --> 00:14:56,733
What do you mean?

287
00:14:57,467 --> 00:14:59,267
We'll make him wait.

288
00:14:59,367 --> 00:15:00,800
That'll buy us some time, right?

289
00:15:02,133 --> 00:15:02,967
While he waits,

290
00:15:03,133 --> 00:15:05,000
we'll search
if there's really a treasure.

291
00:15:06,733 --> 00:15:08,300
I don't know, Gio.

292
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,300
It's a long shot.

293
00:15:09,467 --> 00:15:10,700
So be it.

294
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,300
Unless you have
something else in mind?

295
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:21,967
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

296
00:15:26,633 --> 00:15:27,633
Ouch, Raphie!

297
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:29,767
Were you listening
to their conversation?

298
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:30,933
I just passed by.

299
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:33,367
I wanted to see Sir Martin.

300
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:38,633
I'm his assistant, remember?
Maybe he needed something.

301
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,067
Sure, that's your version
of the story.

302
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:45,833
You're running out of excuses.

303
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:48,500
[SARI]
What's important is I was right.

304
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:50,033
My grandfather was right.

305
00:15:51,433 --> 00:15:52,833
There's treasure hidden.

306
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:53,967
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

307
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,233
You're really proud of that?

308
00:15:55,367 --> 00:15:56,833
[TRIXIE] For real?

309
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,733
There's treasure hunting now
in the Philippines?

310
00:15:59,867 --> 00:16:02,733
[MONETTE] Oh, I'm not so sure
about that treasure hunt.

311
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:04,800
But I remember...

312
00:16:04,933 --> 00:16:07,500
hearing Papa talk about that
when he was alive.

313
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:10,067
Oh, I'm not sure, Monette.

314
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,333
I don't remember.

315
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:13,833
I was just a little girl then,
remember?

316
00:16:14,367 --> 00:16:15,500
[MONETTE] Right.

317
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:18,167
But that's always been
the talk here on the island.

318
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:20,500
They say
there's a lost treasure.

319
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:22,767
I thought it was just a tale.

320
00:16:25,867 --> 00:16:29,267
Oh, Cheska. You've got something
on your mind. What is it?

321
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,567
That's a great material
for my podcast.

322
00:16:31,867 --> 00:16:33,333
I need to film that, Monette.

323
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,667
<i> And I want you to know...</i>

324
00:16:35,767 --> 00:16:37,367
[INAUDIBLE, STATIC NOISE]

325
00:16:37,533 --> 00:16:40,500
[INAUDIBLE]

326
00:16:40,633 --> 00:16:42,400
<i> And I want you to know...</i>

327
00:16:42,567 --> 00:16:44,033
[STATIC NOISE]

328
00:16:44,167 --> 00:16:45,300
[SIGHS EXASPERATEDLY]

329
00:16:46,067 --> 00:16:47,033
Papa.

330
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:50,967
Please help us
decode your video.

331
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:58,533
Hey! [CHESKA CHUCKLES]

332
00:16:58,667 --> 00:16:59,867
Cheska!

333
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:01,600
That was high-pitched.

334
00:17:01,733 --> 00:17:03,033
You're jumpy now, bro?

335
00:17:04,167 --> 00:17:06,367
I don't have time
to fool around with you.

336
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:10,700
What's that, bro?

337
00:17:11,633 --> 00:17:13,700
You're watching
your Dad's video?

338
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:15,467
Let me see it.

339
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:17,467
You'll just mess things up.

340
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:18,900
Ouch.

341
00:17:19,033 --> 00:17:21,000
Is that really
what you think of me, bro?

342
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:22,833
Bro, I'm serious about this.

343
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,333
[CHESKA] And?
I take this seriously, too.

344
00:17:26,267 --> 00:17:27,433
Come on, let me see it.

345
00:17:27,533 --> 00:17:29,100
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:30,167
You're watching that

347
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:31,933
because of the treasure,
aren't you?

348
00:17:34,367 --> 00:17:35,300
Yes.

349
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:38,667
[TONGUE CLICKS] Fine, bro.

350
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:40,400
Here's how it goes. Don't worry.

351
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:43,433
I won't ask you for a part
of your share of the treasure.

352
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:45,833
Bro, I don't care
about my share.

353
00:17:45,967 --> 00:17:49,433
I just want to know if Papa said
anything about the treasure.

354
00:17:49,633 --> 00:17:50,867
But here, watch this.

355
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,967
- [INAUDIBLE, STATIC NOISE]
- Look.

356
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:57,800
- It's corrupted
- Yes.

357
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:01,133
[SCOFFS] That was your problem?

358
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:03,300
Why?

359
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:04,533
Can you fix it?

360
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:07,600
[SCOFFS]

361
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,633
So you changed your mind?

362
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,200
If it's for Leon,

363
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:16,800
I'll take you
as the hotel's partner.

364
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:21,800
Then I should've told you
what I know a long time ago.

365
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,833
If only I knew that's what
you need to change your mind.

366
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:27,500
But you'll have to wait.

367
00:18:27,667 --> 00:18:28,833
Getting the paperwork done
will take some time.

368
00:18:28,933 --> 00:18:31,533
Luna, my dear, I've been in
the business for a long time.

369
00:18:31,700 --> 00:18:33,033
I know the process.

370
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,200
But alright.

371
00:18:36,067 --> 00:18:37,067
I'll wait.

372
00:18:38,733 --> 00:18:41,000
Just make sure
Leon will be out of jail.

373
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:42,067
Just do your part,

374
00:18:43,033 --> 00:18:44,000
and I'll do mine.

375
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:46,133
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

376
00:18:46,233 --> 00:18:50,000
- [MUSIC TURNS TENSE]
- [FOOTSTEPS LIMPING]

377
00:18:55,133 --> 00:18:56,033
[MAN 1] What now?

378
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,667
I'll take care of it.
I got this one.

379
00:18:57,767 --> 00:18:58,700
[MAN 2] Get some soup too.

380
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,333
Wait for me there.
Miss, we'll get three.

381
00:19:16,433 --> 00:19:17,900
[MAN 2] There we go.
That looks good.

382
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,200
[MAN 1] Almazan? Justin?

383
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,767
[MAN 2] I thought it's him.

384
00:19:31,467 --> 00:19:32,900
But it was his brother
who's in jail.

385
00:19:34,067 --> 00:19:35,200
[MAN 1] Leon?

386
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,700
The eldest killed someone?

387
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:39,867
[MAN 2] The young man's body
was found in his car.

388
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:43,067
I see him sometimes
at the station.

389
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:46,300
[MAN 1] Oh, yeah. Soliman.

390
00:19:47,167 --> 00:19:48,533
Juan Soliman.

391
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:52,200
[MAN 2] Dela Paz said
he was looking for his father.

392
00:19:53,133 --> 00:19:54,900
You think he saw him
before he died?

393
00:19:56,233 --> 00:19:59,100
Then the dad
should've taken his body.

394
00:19:59,767 --> 00:20:01,200
[MAN 1] The Almazans
are really something.

395
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,033
The men in that family
are always causing trouble.

396
00:20:04,867 --> 00:20:06,133
Let's just eat.

397
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:15,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

398
00:20:18,533 --> 00:20:19,667
[AMBIENT NATURE NOISE]

399
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:26,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

400
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:29,400
What?

401
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:31,567
Did you see anything?

402
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:35,667
Tsk. There's nothing.

403
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:37,767
Actually, I don't even know

404
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:39,267
what I'm supposed to be
looking at.

405
00:20:40,033 --> 00:20:41,000
How about you?

406
00:20:41,133 --> 00:20:43,100
What clues can you find
in the compass?

407
00:20:44,133 --> 00:20:45,967
There are numbers,
but I don't know what for.

408
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:47,200
Let me see.

409
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:49,467
[MARTIN] Wait, what's that?

410
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:51,533
The serial number
of the compass.

411
00:20:52,867 --> 00:20:54,433
Maybe a vault code?

412
00:20:55,133 --> 00:20:56,600
Papa didn't own a vault.

413
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:58,433
Oh, I don't know.

414
00:20:58,567 --> 00:21:00,667
I'm just wondering
what those numbers are for.

415
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:04,367
[KIKO] Martin!

416
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,800
What's wrong?

417
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:07,600
- Our problem has been solved.
- Huh?

418
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:08,867
Cheska did it.

419
00:21:09,867 --> 00:21:12,067
She restored the corrupted part
of Papa's video.

420
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,333
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

421
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:16,867
[CHAIRS THUD]

422
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,400
Cheska fixed it?

423
00:21:18,533 --> 00:21:19,800
How?

424
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:21,067
She said she found it
on the internet.

425
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,967
There's an app
that fixes the video.

426
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:24,367
Just an app and it's fixed?

427
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:26,367
[KIKO] That's what she said.

428
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:29,800
But not all the corrupted files
have been restored.

429
00:21:30,433 --> 00:21:32,300
But at least we got some of it.

430
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:36,567
Come on, play it.

431
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:41,000
- [KEYBOARD CLACKS]
- This is not an ordinary hotel.

432
00:21:43,467 --> 00:21:46,533
<i>There are many
good memories made here.</i>

433
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:49,833
[MICHAEL] So please,

434
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:52,600
<i> don't sell Hotel 88.</i>

435
00:21:52,733 --> 00:21:56,200
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

436
00:21:56,367 --> 00:21:58,167
[MICHAEL]
<i> Not just for the business,</i>

437
00:21:58,267 --> 00:21:59,600
<i> not for the money.</i>

438
00:22:00,467 --> 00:22:02,833
<i> Because this is your home.</i>

439
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:07,833
<i> And I want you to know...</i>

440
00:22:08,533 --> 00:22:10,333
that there is a hidden treasure

441
00:22:11,033 --> 00:22:12,533
<i> here in this hotel.</i>

442
00:22:13,367 --> 00:22:20,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

443
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:26,733
We didn't get a clue...

444
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:30,067
or more info about the clue.

445
00:22:31,233 --> 00:22:32,767
But this only means one thing.

446
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:36,300
The treasure is real.

447
00:22:39,167 --> 00:22:41,467
And we were not wasting
our time looking for it.

448
00:22:44,567 --> 00:22:47,067
All our efforts are not in vain.

449
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:51,267
[KIKO] This is it.

450
00:22:53,333 --> 00:22:55,000
This is the beginning
of our search

451
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:56,967
for the hidden treasure
at Hotel 88.

452
00:22:57,100 --> 00:23:01,667
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

453
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:03,333
<i> I tried everything.</i>

454
00:23:03,467 --> 00:23:05,233
<i>I've checked it in the light,
in the dark,</i>

455
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:06,733
<i> in the trees, in the clouds!</i>

456
00:23:06,967 --> 00:23:08,733
<i> Do you trust me, sir?</i>

457
00:23:08,833 --> 00:23:11,000
<i>It could be related
to Gio's compass.</i>

458
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:12,633
<i> The numbers are coordinates?</i>

459
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:14,500
<i> It seems like it.</i>

460
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:17,400
<i> The priority is the treasure.</i>

461
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:19,433
<i> The priority is Leon.</i>

462
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:21,767
Why are there highlighted words?

463
00:23:23,367 --> 00:23:24,167
<i> Jade,</i>

464
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:26,367
<i> maybe it makes up a sentence?</i>

465
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:27,933
<i> Martin is going to kill me.</i>
